---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/site-layout.astro';

const featuredStates = [
  { name: 'Ohio', slug: 'ohio', label: 'First draft state guide' },
  { name: 'Wyoming', slug: 'wyoming', label: 'Fast, low-friction launch state' },
  { name: 'New York', slug: 'new-york', label: 'High intent, high search opportunity' },
  { name: 'New Mexico', slug: 'new-mexico', label: 'Strong privacy angle' },
  { name: 'California', slug: 'california', label: 'Expensive, but massive demand' },
  { name: 'Colorado', slug: 'colorado', label: 'Straightforward filing process' },
];
---

<SiteLayout
  title="LLCAtlas | Form Your LLC Without Guesswork"
  description="Opinionated LLC formation guides that help founders choose the right path and the right filing partner."
>
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <span class="inline-flex rounded-full bg-amber-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-semibold text-amber-900">
      Free LLC formation guides for high-intent founders
    </span>

    <div class="space-y-5">
      <h1>Form your LLC with less noise and one clear recommendation.</h1>
      <p class="max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-600">
        LLCAtlas is a focused content funnel for founders comparing LLC formation options. We
        simplify the process, call out the tradeoffs, and point readers to the best-value partner
        instead of dumping them into a generic list.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
      <a
        id="primary-cta"
        href="#featured-states"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-amber-500 px-6 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-950 transition hover:bg-amber-400"
      >
        Explore the first state guides
      </a>
      <a
        href="#how-it-works"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 px-6 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 transition hover:border-slate-400 hover:bg-slate-50"
      >
        See the page structure
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid gap-4 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">Positioning</p>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-700">Opinionated guidance, not neutral directories.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">Monetization</p>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-700">Affiliate CTAs to registered agent and formation partners.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">V1 scope</p>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-700">Homepage, five state guides, and one comparison page.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="featured-states" class="space-y-6">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <h2>Initial state pages</h2>
      <p class="max-w-2xl">
        These are placeholder cards for the first SEO entry points. The eventual goal is one shared
        template that turns each state into a conversion-focused guide instead of a generic article.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3">
      {
        featuredStates.map((state) => (
          <a
            href={`/llc/${state.slug}`}
            class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5 transition hover:border-slate-300 hover:bg-slate-50"
          >
            <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-950">{state.name} LLC Formation</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">{state.label}</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
              Placeholder for filing fees, timeline, process steps, and a single recommendation.
            </p>
          </a>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6 rounded-3xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <h2>What this homepage needs to do</h2>
      <p class="max-w-3xl">
        The homepage is a router, not a masterpiece. Its job is to explain the offer quickly,
        establish trust, and send users into high-intent state pages and the comparison page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-5">
        <h3>Reduce confusion</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Surface the filing costs, timeline, and requirements without making people hunt through
          state sites.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-5">
        <h3>Take a stance</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Recommend one partner clearly, with enough reasoning to remove decision fatigue.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-5">
        <h3>Drive one action</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Push users toward the best LLC service page or their state guide, then into the affiliate
          click.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="how-it-works" class="space-y-6">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <h2>Planned site flow</h2>
      <p class="max-w-3xl">
        Every future page should follow the same pattern: verdict first, proof second, CTA repeated
        at natural decision points.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ol class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">Step 1</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3">Capture search intent</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Target high-intent queries like state formation pages and LLC service comparisons.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">Step 2</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3">Answer the actual question</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Cover fees, process, timing, and whether a state or provider is the right fit.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">Step 3</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3">Convert with one obvious CTA</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Present a decisive recommendation with a clear path into the affiliate partner.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <div slot="sidebar" class="space-y-4">
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">Primary CTA</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl">Start with the best LLC service page.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
        This space is reserved for the highest-intent recommendation and affiliate CTA.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/best-llc-services"
        class="mt-5 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-slate-950 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-slate-800"
      >
        View best LLC services
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-500">Placeholder rail</p>
      <ul class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600">
        <li>Top affiliate recommendation</li>
        <li>Quick state navigation</li>
        <li>Trust note and disclosure</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
